{"abstract":[{"text":"A wrapper for the POSIX ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"stat()"},{"text":" function. The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"stat()"},{"text":" function","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"returns information about a file. On Windows the ","type":"text"},{"code":"stat()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" function in"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the C library checks only the FAT-style READONLY attribute and does"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"not look at the ACL at all. Thus on Windows the protection bits in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the "},{"code":"st_mode","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" field are a fabrication of little use."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"stat","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"filename","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SP","text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gchar","text":"gchar","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":">!) -> "},{"text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"On Windows the Microsoft C libraries have several variants of the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"stat struct and "},{"code":"stat()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" function with names like ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_stat()"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_stat32()"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_stat32i64()"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"code":"_stat64i32()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". The one used here is for 32-bit code"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the one with 32-bit size and time fields, specifically called "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_stat32()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In Microsoft’s compiler, by default struct stat means one with","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"64-bit time fields while in MinGW struct stat is the legacy one"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with 32-bit fields. To hopefully clear up this messs, the gstdio.h","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"header defines a type ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StatBuf"},{"text":" which is the appropriate struct type","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"depending on the platform and\/or compiler being used. On POSIX it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is just struct stat, but note that even on POSIX platforms, "},{"code":"stat()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"might be a macro."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"See your C library manual for more details about ","type":"text"},{"code":"stat()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StatBuf","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StatBuf\/StatBufProtocol-Implementations"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"metadata":{"symbolKind":"method","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib15StatBufProtocolPAAE4stat8filenameSiSPys4Int8VGSg_tF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib7StatBufC","title":"stat(filename:)","roleHeading":"Instance Method","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"stat"},{"tex